est yet — stole the spotlight.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eWe still don’t know much about the Samsung Galaxy S25 Edge. Visitors at the MWC 2025 didn’t receive any information on it, and were not allowed to touch it. But we do know that like the rest of the Galaxy S25 series, and much like the other buzzy phones debuted at MWC, it will have a host of AI integration features (including built-in Google Gemini features) and advanced \u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;External link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://news.samsung.com/us/samsung-solidifies-mobile-ai-leadership-mwc-2025-galaxy-ai-software-centric-networks/\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://news.samsung.com/us/samsung-solidifies-mobile-ai-leadership-mwc-2025-galaxy-ai-software-centric-networks/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"\u003ecamera technology\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eThe super-thin phone is likely to launch in the coming months, as rival Apple (\u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;External link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://qz.com/quote/AAPL\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://qz.com/quote/AAPL\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"\u003eAAPL\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e) is also reportedly readying to unveil a super-thin phone of its own with the highly anticipated and rumored \u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;External link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://qz.com/tariffs-can-t-bring-apple-down-new-m4-equipped-macbook-1851767827\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://qz.com/tariffs-can-t-bring-apple-down-new-m4-equipped-macbook-1851767827\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"\u003eiPhone 17 Air\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cfigure id=\"\" data-id=\"b63373fa6d576664a7c2ae0309e72fd4\" data-recommend-id=\"image://b63373fa6d576664a7c2ae0309e72fd4\" data-format=\"png\" data-width=\"1796\" data-height=\"904\" data-lightbox=\"false\" data-recommended=\"false\" data-hide=\"false\" contenteditable=\"false\" draggable=\"false\"\u003e\u003cdiv contenteditable=\"false\" data-link-reference=\"\" data-link-target=\"\" data-syndicationrights=\"false\" data-imagerights=\"other-license\" data-hide=\"false\" data-hidecredit=\"false\"\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource media=\"(max-width: 49.94em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_965/b63373fa6d576664a7c2ae0309e72fd4.jpg\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 50em) and (max-width: 63.69em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_1315/b63373fa6d576664a7c2ae0309e72fd4.jpg\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 63.75em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_1600/b63373fa6d576664a7c2ae0309e72fd4.jpg\"/\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"Image for article titled You\u0026amp;#39;ll Probably Be Using Some Of These Gadgets From MCW 2025 Very Soon\" data-chomp-id=\"b63373fa6d576664a7c2ae0309e72fd4\" data-format=\"png\" data-height=\"904\" data-alt=\"Image for article titled You\u0026amp;#39;ll Probably Be Using Some Of These Gadgets From MCW 2025 Very Soon\" data-anim-src=\"\" src=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_645/b63373fa6d576664a7c2ae0309e72fd4.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/picture\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eScreenshot: Lenovo (\u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;External link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://news.lenovo.com/pressroom/press-releases/expanding-boundaries-ai-powered-creativity-productivity-and-innovation/\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://news.lenovo.com/pressroom/press-releases/expanding-boundaries-ai-powered-creativity-productivity-and-innovation/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"\u003eOther\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e)\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cspan data-id=\"b63373fa6d576664a7c2ae0309e72fd4\" data-recommend-id=\"image://b63373fa6d576664a7c2ae0309e72fd4\" data-format=\"png\" data-width=\"1796\" data-height=\"904\" data-lightbox=\"false\" data-recommended=\"false\" data-hide=\"false\"\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003eLenovo also caught attention with another concept: a PC that runs on solar energy.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eThe device has a solar panel that leverages “black contact cell” technology to achieve an over 24% conversion rate, which Lenovo \u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;External link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://news.lenovo.com/pressroom/press-releases/expanding-boundaries-ai-powered-creativity-productivity-and-innovation/\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://news.lenovo.com/pressroom/press-releases/expanding-boundaries-ai-powered-creativity-productivity-and-innovation/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"\u003eclaims\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e is “one of the highest in the industry.” Just 20 minutes of direct sunlight can power the PC for one hour of video playback, according to the company. That means if you live somewhere that gets enough sunlight, you might not need to worry about charging ports and cables if you want to work outside on a bright day.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eMuch like the foldable Flip PC, Lenovo’s Yoga Solar PC is still an early concept and the company didn’t share a production plan.\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cfigure id=\"\" data-id=\"f0a6191873abb3dd5b7690cd15e250c1\" data-recommend-id=\"image://f0a6191873abb3dd5b7690cd15e250c1\" data-format=\"png\" data-width=\"1350\" data-height=\"958\" data-lightbox=\"false\" data-recommended=\"false\" data-hide=\"false\" contenteditable=\"false\" draggable=\"false\"\u003e\u003cdiv contenteditable=\"false\" data-link-reference=\"\" data-link-target=\"\" data-syndicationrights=\"false\" data-imagerights=\"other-license\" data-hide=\"false\" data-hidecredit=\"false\"\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource media=\"(max-width: 49.94em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_965/f0a6191873abb3dd5b7690cd15e250c1.jpg\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 50em) and (max-width: 63.69em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_1315/f0a6191873abb3dd5b7690cd15e250c1.jpg\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 63.75em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_1600/f0a6191873abb3dd5b7690cd15e250c1.jpg\"/\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"Image for article titled You\u0026amp;#39;ll Probably Be Using Some Of These Gadgets From MCW 2025 Very Soon\" data-chomp-id=\"f0a6191873abb3dd5b7690cd15e250c1\" data-format=\"png\" data-height=\"958\" data-alt=\"Image for article titled You\u0026amp;#39;ll Probably Be Using Some Of These Gadgets From MCW 2025 Very Soon\" data-anim-src=\"\" src=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_645/f0a6191873abb3dd5b7690cd15e250c1.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/picture\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eScreenshot: Nothing Tech (\u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;External link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://us.nothing.tech/pages/phone-3a?srsltid=AfmBOoqZbhxn3753a7vDZNnNB4HdKp5pPxdoraz6mq5SqylZvzOwMyLE\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://us.nothing.tech/pages/phone-3a?srsltid=AfmBOoqZbhxn3753a7vDZNnNB4HdKp5pPxdoraz6mq5SqylZvzOwMyLE\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"\u003eOther\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e)\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cspan data-id=\"f0a6191873abb3dd5b7690cd15e250c1\" data-recommend-id=\"image://f0a6191873abb3dd5b7690cd15e250c1\" data-format=\"png\" data-width=\"1350\" data-height=\"958\" data-lightbox=\"false\" data-recommended=\"false\" data-hide=\"false\"\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003eLondon-based \u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;External link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://us.nothing.tech/pages/phone-3a#phone3a-watch-video-template--18566579323032__main\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://us.nothing.tech/pages/phone-3a#phone3a-watch-video-template--18566579323032__main\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"\u003eNothing’s\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e new 3A and 3A Pro smartphones were all the rage in Barcelona this week, and not just for their AI features, which include an assistant that compiles important information from photos and screenshots you deem essential. The phones also drew attention for their fun designs and relatively low price point.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eThe phones, which boast a futuristic-looking translucent back and LED lights that flash whenever you receive a notification, start at $379 for the 3A and $459 for the 3A Pro. Both devices are available now for pre-order in the U.S., as part of the company’s \u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;External link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://us.nothing.tech/pages/beta-program?utm_medium=Affiliate\u0026amp;utm_source=Awin\u0026amp;sv_campaign_id=78888\u0026amp;sv_tax1=affiliate\u0026amp;sv_tax2=\u0026amp;sv_tax3=Skimlinks\u0026amp;sv_tax4=theverge.com\u0026amp;sv_affiliate_id=78888\u0026amp;awc=48011_1741369467_84068a90a4361cf8d030df3aeaebd20d\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://us.nothing.tech/pages/beta-program?utm_medium=Affiliate\u0026amp;utm_source=Awin\u0026amp;sv_campaign_id=78888\u0026amp;sv_tax1=affiliate\u0026amp;sv_tax2=\u0026amp;sv_tax3=Skimlinks\u0026amp;sv_tax4=theverge.com\u0026amp;sv_affiliate_id=78888\u0026amp;awc=48011_1741369467_84068a90a4361cf8d030df3aeaebd20d\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"\u003ebeta\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e launch in the U.S. market.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003eThis story originally appeared on Quartz, our sister site, on Friday, March 7.\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
